e time, including the women’s rights movement and the campaign for the vote. Perhaps more importantly, the discussion surrounding women’s self-defense revealed powerful myths about the source of violence against women and opened up conversations about the less visible violence that many women faced in their own homes. Through self-defense training, women debunked patriarchal myths about inherent feminine weakness, creating a new image of women as powerful and self-reliant. Whether or not women consciously pursued self-defense for these reasons, their actions embodied feminist politics. Although their individual motivations may have varied, their collective action echoed through the twentieth century, demanding emancipation from the constrictions that prevented women from exercising their full rights as citizens and human beings. This book is a fascinating and comprehensive introduction to one of the most important women’s issues of all time. This book will provoke good debate and offer distinct responses and solutions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aFeminismzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSelf-defense for womenzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSelf-defensexSocial aspectszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSocial movementszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aWomenxPolitical activityzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aWomenzUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 0aWomen's rightszUnited StatesxHistory. 7aSPORTS & RECREATION / Martial Arts & Self-Defense.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831107289720 cprintz978147982853140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479872763423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479872763/original  a978-3-11-072897-2  New York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKAL